A former governor of Oyo State, Senator Rasidi Ladoja on Thursday officially announced his defection for the Africa Democratic Congress (ADC) to the Zenith Labour Party (ZLP). He said his decision to leave ADC was as a result of the injustice in the party. The former governor who spoke at his Bodija country home, said he was not consulted before taking salient decisions in the party. Details later…. Ladoja joins Zenith Labour, picks Alli as guber candidate Oyo 2019: Political heavyweights regroup under Obasanjo’s ADC to unseat APC Mimiko withdraws from Presidential race, to run for Senate